## C3 = Carmichael number of the form (60h + 43) (180h + 127) * (300h + 211)
##   - all terms are primes, 3 mod 4
##   - from Chernick Carmichael(3) form (15k +13) (45k +37) * (75k + 61)
##     - k = 4*h + 2, which results in 3 mod 4
##
## see Rabin: Probabilistic algorithm for testing primality
##   section 1, p. 133
##   Journal of Number Theory, 12, 128-138, 1980
##   www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022314X80900840
##   [accessed 2023-10-11]
